DIGEST
SB 109 Original 2026 Regular Session Jenkins
Present law provides for the membership of the La. Emergency Medical Services
Commission within the La. Dept. of Health.
Present law provides for 12 voting members appointed by the governor.
Present law provides for two members that are emergency medical services administrators,
including one representing the private sector and one representing the public sector.
Proposed law retains present law and requires the emergency medical services administrator
members to be nominated by the La. Ambulance Alliance.
Present law provides for two licensed paramedics and one licensed emergency medical
technician who are approved as emergency medical services educators by the bureau, with
at least one of the members appointed by the La. Fire Chiefs Association.
Proposed law retains present law and removes the requirement for the members to be
approved as emergency medical services educators by the bureau.
Present law provides for one member who is, at a minimum, a state-certified emergency
medical technician nominated by the La. Municipal Association.
Proposed law retains present law and requires the member to be state-licensed instead of
state-certified.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 40:1133.3(B)(1)(a), (b), and (d))
